-- 
2011-04-14T10:38:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-14/senegal-aims-to-jump-50-places-in-business-ranking-soleil-says.html
Senegal  will reduce administrative
delays and boost access to credit to help the country leap 50
places in the  World Bank â€™s  Doing Business survey , Le Soleil
said, citing Prime Minister Soulayemane Ndene Ndiaye.  The state will streamline the system for obtaining
construction permits and shorten the time it takes to get
business permits and transfer property, Ndiaye said at a cabinet
meeting yesterday, according to Le Soleil.  The West African nation ranked 152nd out of 183 on the ease
of doing business list compiled by the World Bank.  To contact the reporter on this story:
